The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, September 19, 2004 

 More areas go under water

 OUR BUREAU

 Sept. 18: The flood situation in Nadia, North 24 Parganas, Birbhum, Murshidabad and Burdwan districts remained grim with more areas getting inundated over the last 24 hours. The lives of nearly seven lakh people have been affected.

 An alert was sounded yesterday in Birbhum and Murshidabad after as rain over the past 10 days flooded low-lying areas in Nadia and North 24-Parganas.

 State relief minister Hafiz Alam Sairani said he would visit the flood-affected areas of North 24 Parganas ? Bongaon, Bagda and Gaighata ? tomorrow. ?We are sending relief material and the situation is expected to improve,? the minister said. At least 120 relief centres were opened in the five districts, he said.

 Gaighata block development officer Prashanta Adhikari said two more persons died during the last two days. 




